Package org.jdiscript.handlers

Class BaseEventHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jdiscript.handlers.BaseEventHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DebugEventHandler, DebugLocatableHandler, DebugWatchpointHandler, OnAccessWatchpoint, OnBreakpoint, OnClassPrepare, OnClassUnload, OnEvent, OnException, OnLocatable, OnMethodEntry, OnMethodExit, OnModificationWatchpoint, OnMonitorContendedEnter, OnMonitorContendedEntered, OnMonitorWait, OnMonitorWaited, OnStep, OnThreadDeath, OnThreadStart, OnVMDeath, OnVMDisconnect, OnVMStart, OnWatchpoint
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Once
    public class BaseEventHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements OnAccessWatchpoint, OnBreakpoint, OnClassPrepare, OnClassUnload, OnEvent, OnException, OnLocatable, OnMethodEntry, OnMethodExit, OnModificationWatchpoint, OnMonitorContendedEnter, OnMonitorContendedEntered, OnMonitorWait, OnMonitorWaited, OnStep, OnThreadDeath, OnThreadStart, OnVMDeath, OnVMDisconnect, OnVMStart, OnWatchpoint
    Each handler method for requested events delegates to unhandledEvent(), which throws an UnhandledEventException. Handler methods for unrequested events do nothing. This class is intended to be subclassed.
